author: Ralph Wood
title: Fresnan Wins IRONMAN
text:
Fresnan Wins IRONMAN - KMPH FOX 26 | Central San Joaquin Valley News Source Member Center: rwood@kmph.com Fresno - 
Fresno's Chris Montross has won the world championship at Hawaii's IRONMAN Triathlon. The 55-year-old took the title for his age group at the prestigious endurance event. 
The IRONMAN Triathlon is a 2.4 mile swim, a 112 mile bike ride, and a full marathon of 26.2 miles. Montross covered the 140.6 miles in Kailua-Kona in ten hours, six minutes and 35 seconds.
